    • Constructor Detail

      • AttributeMap

        public AttributeMap(java.lang.String sourceAttribute,
            java.lang.String destinationAttribute,
            AttributeType type)
        Create a new attribute map using this constructor. The sourceAttribute and destinationAttribute parameters refer to the source and destination attribute names respectively that are to be mapped as found in their respective tables. The type parameter indicates whether the datatype of the attributes to be mapped is of form AttributeType.STRING or AttributeType.NUMERICAL.
        Parameters:
        sourceAttribute - attribute name in the source table
        destinationAttribute - corresponding attribute name in the destination table
        type - specifies whether the attribute is of type AttributeType.STRING or AttributeType.NUMERICAL, as defined in the enum AttributeType.
        See Also:
        AttributeType, AttributeType.STRING, AttributeType.NUMERICAL
